		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was thinking more along the lines of making a mm1+your covers, type of distro. That's why I said nevermind. Unless you're ok with distributing them for free like that? I figured not because they were on bandcamp (love that site and idea). You mentioned that you use additional audio cips for these remakes; only vrc6?  Not sure if I have enough cpu resource to emulate that chip extension, if I did a PSG only implementation (no CDDA) of your tracks (famitracker?). I have two free PCE channels and one free ADPCM channel (with dedicated 64k of ram), though I don't emulate DPCM for the NES so I would assume ADPCM would be used for that. And of course, you wanted to do such a project.

		

